
[1]malignity

   MALIG'NITY, n. [L. malignitas.] Extreme enmity, or evil dispositions of
   heart towards another; malice without provocation, or malevolence with
   baseness of heart; deep rooted spite.

   1. Virulence; destructive tendency; as the malignity of an ulcer or
   disease.

   2. Extreme evilness of nature; as the malignity of fraud.

   3. Extreme sinfulness; enormity or heinousness; as the malignity of
   sin.
